<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- C major: no accidentals needed, clean open voicing throughout.
- Measures 2, 4, 7: Four different chords per bar — each beat a new chord. RH 2-note thirds, LH 3-4 note open.
- Measures 3, 8: Ascending arpeggios in RH (C and G respectively) while LH sustains open voicing.
- Measure 6: RH descending inner voice motion against sustained LH — independent lines.
- Measure 9: F half-note with inner voice motion — textural contrast.
- B° (vii°): B-D-F in LH (open diminished fifth B-F), D-F in RH — distinctive sound at m7 beat 3.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Measure 2: Dm→C→Am→G (all four diatonic chords in succession); LH steps down D→C→A→G in bass.
- Measure 7: F→C→B°→C — the B° creates half-step resolution in bass (B→C) and inner voice (F→E).
- Measure 10: G held for 3 beats, RH adds third-voice on final beat for gentle close.

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1-2: Light opening — 2-voice RH, 4-note LH on downbeats only; measure 2 full harmonic activity.
- mm. 3-4: Arpeg in m3 contrasts block chords in m4; building motion.
- mm. 5-6: High melodic register (E5); LH sustains while RH has inner-voice life.
- mm. 7-8: Chromatic color (B°), then G arpeg for balance.
- mm. 9-11: Relaxing to final C; suspension/passing motion in m9-10, convergent whole-note cadence.
-->
